Every #MTGWAR card will be previewed within the first three weeks of April.

Mythic Championship London will have a new mulligan rule. You will now draw seven cards every time you mulligan. When you are satisfied, you will put cards back on the bottom of your library for each time you mulligan. There will no longer be any scrying after mulliganing.

If the test goes well, Wizards will look to implement this in all formats around the summer release of M20.

If the test goes poorly, they will go back to the drawing board and keep the current mulligan rule.

Core Set 2020 #MTGM20 will release July 12

Previews will start in mid- to late-June


Commander precons are coming August 23 with four decks. Previews will start in August.
